# CI/CD

- **Fail fast:** lint → typecheck → test → build; block merge on red CI.
- **Reproducible:** `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`; commit lockfile; Node/pnpm versions pinned in CI.
- **Concurrency:** cancel in-progress runs for the same PR/branch where useful.
- **Secrets:** only GitHub Actions secrets / OIDC — never in workflow YAML or logs.
- **Stages:** unit + integration (with DB service if needed); optional e2e on critical paths; `pnpm audit` (or equivalent) in CI.
- **Deploy:** migrations strategy per `06-database.mdc` — do not hand-delete failed migrations; backup before risky changes.
- **Managed hosts (Vercel, Railway, Render, Fly):** use platform env + health checks; full Dockerfile/K8s only when self-hosting.
- **Feature flags:** document each flag; remove after full rollout; log which variant served.
- **Dependency policy:** patch quickly; minor after changelog review; major as planned work with tests.

**Templates:** `docs/reference/workflows/ci-quality.yml.example`, extended patterns previously in this file now belong in `docs/reference/` or team docs — keep `.mdc` lean.
